  • Carrier/Reporter: R & L CARRIERS, INC.
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Description: On August 10, 2023, two (2) 5-pound bags of sodium carbonate peroxyhydrate were torn during transit and released approximately one (1) pound of product to the trailer interior. R+L Carriers retained Cura Emergency Services, LC who dispatched a crew from GrayMar Environmental (GME) to remediate the impacted site. GME personnel utilized hand tools to collect and containerize all impacted material into one (1) 55-gallon drum for disposal.

item.title: Report X-2023080654
item.description:
Report X-2023080654

Identified by scraper @ 2023-08-31T21:11:21+00:00

  • Incident Date: 2023-08-03
  • City: SALEM
  • State: OR
  • Report Type: A hazardous material incident
  • Mode Of Transportation: Highway
  • Carrier/Reporter: Fedex Ground Package System, Inc.
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Description: SequenceEvent: At 5AM on 8/3/2023, QA was called to DOOR 18 for a possible HazMat leak in Trailer #828018. QA responded and upon arrival a QA employee smelled an intense aroma. The unexplained aroma was coming from the potential leaking HazMat. HazMat was immediately taken to the HazMat cage and was placed under the vent. Proper QA HazMat was followed. upon inspection with in the HazMat cage, a package with 6 containers of Diethyl Ether was inspected. One out of six containers was found completely empty with a loose cap. QA precautions were taken and proper protocol was followed. DescribePack: One of the bottles had a loose cap. DurationRel: 1 and MitigateEffect: HazMat was immediately taken to the HazMat cage and dealt with accordingly.

  • Report Type: A hazardous material incident
  • Mode Of Transportation: Highway
  • Carrier/Reporter: XPO LOGISTICS, LLC
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Description: XPO Logistics terminal UPO experienced a UN1950 Gunk - Chlorinated Brake Parts Cleaner release from a box containing (12) 20-ounce aerosol cans. ERTS dispatched contractors to conduct cleanup operations. Contractors arrived onsite and confirmed approximately 20-ounces of product released impacting the box/packaging only due to a forklift puncture. The damaged box containing (12) 20-ounce cans of product were placed into a 5-gallon poly drum. The waste was staged onsite for terminal personnel to manage.
